Rauvolfia serpentina

   [9185.jpg]
    Authority   (L.) Benth. ex Kurz
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Gentianales:Apocynaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9185

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Nair P 1980 pp 315-316 [LIG, RAIN, DRA, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 285 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 26 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb, which rotts may be harvested after 2-3 years. Seeds can
   ripen throughout the year but the main season is the cold weather
   period.
   COMMON NAMES
   Java devil pepper, Rauwolfia.
   FURTHER INF
   Java devil pepper can grow up to 1 m in height. It is found in hilly
   areas and on mountain slopes up to 1000 m in elevation. It is best
   adapted to a well-distributed rainfall. Mentioned as a useful
   agroforestry species. Average yield is 2-4 t/ha of air-dried roots per
   year after the third year.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
